 BY TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO A truck driver has crushed a male motorcyclist to death after the victim engaged in wrongful overtaking while riding along Gbongan-Ife route in Osun State. According to the spokeperson of the Osun State Command of the Federal Road Safety Corps, Agnes Ogungbemi, the accident occured around 4:40pm. Ogungbemi said the Okada rider overtook wrongly while plying the expressway before he was hit by an Iveco Eurostar truck with registration number: MKA09ZE. She said the crash happened at St Paul Grammar School, Gbongan, 1.5km from Sasa Bridge adding that the victim, riding a blue colour Jincheng AX100 MC, died on the spot. Out of three persons that were involved in the crash, only one died. “The family of the deceased took over the dead victim while the vehicle involved was taken over by Nigeria Police Force, Gbongan,” Ogungbemi noted. 